RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 91. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 11500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 (MINNESOTA BRED $6,250) OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $6,250. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At One Mile Or Over Since July 26 Al lowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EISENSTAEDT broke well inside, set the pace into the first turn, was prompted from the outside by POLITICAL RIOT near the six and a half furlong mark and briefly headed by that foe near the five eighths, vied inside him, edged out to a defined lead past the half-mile mark, set the pace around the far turn, kept on clear in the lane, felt the crop once midstretch but was otherwise hand ridden and shown the crop from there while holding sway. SIGNOFTHECROSS chased at the rear of a compact main group around the first turn, tracked the leading pair outside of WILLY THE COBBLER down the backstretch, rallied three wide on the far turn, chased the leader down the lane willingly under a drive but proved a clear second best. WILLY THE COBBLER broke at the rear but soon tracked the leading pair while saving ground, continued to track the leading pair inside of SIGNOFTHECROSS down the back straight, saved ground around the far turn while gradually losing ground on the pacesetter, was driven into the lane and chased on mildly as best of the rest. KING NATE settled at the rear, trailed around the clubhouse turn and down the back straight, continued to save ground around the far turn while taking closer order on the other four runners, swung out three wide into the lane and came up empty. POLITICAL RIOT broke near the rear but sent between horses in to the first turn, prompted the pace two wide, briefly headed the leader near the five-furlong mark, briefly vied two wide but was relegated to a two wide stalking poition around the far turn, began to weaken between horses approaching the quarter while hard ridden, and weakened in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 5F Turf CR: 61. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ADIOS MUCHACHAS was herded out by SKY RAVEN at the break, tracked the leading pair outside while positioned three wide, was pushed along two wide past the three eighths and responded with a rally, engaged outside of CRESSONS LIL CHARM turning for home, grazed that foe while coming inward in upper stretch, led near the furlong mark and kicked clear near the sixteenth mark. CRESSONS LIL CHARM broke sharply and was soon clear inside, was clear inside around the bend, was grazed by ADIOS MUCHACHAS in upper stretch as that one engaged to her outside, was headed by that foe near the furlong mark but chased on to hold the place. SKY RAVEN broke extremely awkwardly, settled at the rear of the main group, saved ground on the turn until angling out near the quarter, was carried out by TACTICAL EXPRESS midstretch and chased on mildly for show. TACTICAL EXPRESS stalked the pace early, was pushed along into the turn and ran a bit rankly into the bend, nonetheless continued to track in range, came out on SKY RAVEN near midstretch while chasing inside that foe, flattened out and lost show late. MY LITTLE GYPSY came out sharply at the start, soon trailed, raced in the three to four path on the turn, swung into the lane in the five to six path, and mustered no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 12500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 26 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minn esota Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DON'T BOX ME IN soon cleared to the lead, continued uncontested in the two path down the backstretch and around the far turn, floated into the lane in the four path, continued to drift out but maintained a clear lead under a drive. ZOFFA settled early, raced between horses in the rear flight into the back straight, was carried out by SEEKING SPLENDOR when that one drifted out, took gradually closer order approaching the far turn, swung three wide approaching the five sixteenths, was driven three wide with the stalking flight into the lane, chased on willingly to the finish but could not reel in the pacesetter. BLACK LIMO was bumped by SEEKING SPLENDOR in the opening strides, tracked the pace inside of O DOGG, continued to track inside around the far turn, was no match for the pacesetter into the lane, continued inside of O DOGG and ZOFFA into upper stretch, and was outfinished by ZOFFA in the final sixteenth for the place. PASSTHECAT raced near the rear outside of SEEKING SPLENDOR around the first turn, came into the back straight three wide in the rear group, continued at the rear down the back straight and two wide in the rear pair on the far turn, floated out near the center of the track into upper stretch and ran on mildly past tiring foes. SEEKING SPLENDOR lost the right iron while breaking outward and bumped BLACK LIMO in the opening strides, raced inside toward the rear around the first turn, herded ZOFFA outward into the backstretch while floating out, was pushed along while well behind the leading trio down the backstretch, raced at the inside of the rear pair around the far turn, was driven inside in upper stretch, had no rally, and finished without the jockey ever regaining his iron. O DOGG tracked two wide on the first turn, continued in range two wide down the backstretch, was driven two wide on the far turn but could not mount a threat to the leader, raced between horses in upper stretch and weakened in the final furlong.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR MN-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BURNING LEAVES chased at the inside of the rear trio in a compact pack down the backstretch, was urged inside on the turn in the tracking flight, shifted off the inside past the three sixteenths, responded well under a drive, engaged outside of HAYHAYCAPTAIN JAC approaching the sixteenth, drove to the lead past that point and edged clear. HAYHAYCAPTAIN JAC was hustled to the lead, raced clear in the two path on the far turn, kept on clear to the furlong pole but began to shorten stride, was engaged by BURNING LEAVES, lost the lead to that foe past the sixteenth and kept on for place. BIG BOY MCCOY chased three wide early, raced in the four path near the rear on the turn, chased under a drive in upper stretch, came in and grazed PASSING TIME approaching the furlong mark, got up for place near the sixteenth mark and kept his head narrowly in front of PASSING TIME to the wire while proving no match for the top pair. PASSING TIME tracked outside and just off of HAYHAYCAPTAINJAC, chased two wide around the turn and into the lane, could not keep up with BURNING LEAVES when that one launched a rally from upper stretch, was grazed by BIG BOY MCCOY to his outside near the furlong mark and was outfinished for show through the final sixteenth. J J'S WILDCAT chased between horses early, settled at the rear on the turn, was pushed along at the rear while racing in the two to three path around the bend, and offered no response.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHANNEL WON was bumped by OPTIMAL COURAGE in the opening strides, chased at the rear of a tight main group early, raced between horses on the turn just behind the leading flight, swung four wide into the lane, responded well with a rally, got to the lead near the sixteenth and held stoutly to the finish. MARVELOUS THUNDER was sent for pace inside but outsprinted to the lead, tracked along the inside on the turn, rallied up the rail inside of MISTER BANJOMAN into the lane, kept on willingly to the wire but was outkicked by the winner. OPTIMAL COURAGE broke out and bumped CHANNEL WON in the opening strides, prompted the pace two wide between horses, raced three wide into the lane, kept on under a drive between horses, continued to battle between horses into the final furlong but was narrowly outfinished late. MISTER BANJOMAN disputed the pace at the inside of the leading pack, led narrowly in upper stretch but was engaged from both sides past the three sixteenths, vied to the eighth pole but flattened out between horses in the final furlong. RELEASED broke sharply, attended the pace four wide in the leading pack down the backstretch and around the turn, floated six wide into the turn, chased on but proved no match for the leading trio. HI YAH chased three wide in the tracking flight, swung five wide into upper stretch, angled in and chased on mildly between horses late. HAPPY HOUR BOBBY disputed the early pace three wide in the leading pack, floated five wide into upper stretch and weakened while drifting out. RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JONNY B GONEY was forward early but ultimately outsprinted to the lead by FROSTY VIEW, tracked outside of that foe, was pushed along outside the leader on the turn to keep him in range, continued chasing in range of the leader despite floating out in upper stretch, reeled the pacesetter in under a drive and took the lead near the sixteenth pole. FROSTY VIEW ducked in at the break and broke toward the rear, was nudged up the fence to take the lead, set the pace inside, raced greenly while still on the lead in upper stretch, was engaged by JONNY B GONEY in the final furlong, lost the lead to that foe at the sixteenth and chased on second best. MO MESA chased the leading pair inside of CARPE GOLD and GOT GHOSTED early, continued to chase the leaders inside of GOT GHOSTED on the turn, chased the leading pair willingly down the lane, and continued to take gradually closer order to the finish. COMMISSIONER OSCAR settled near the rear early, was urged three wide on the turn to gain position, floated four wide into the stretch, and chased on mildly to prove best of the rest. GOT GHOSTED tracked the leading pair three wide down the back straight, chased them outside of MO MESA around the turn, was no match for that trio from upper stretch and flattened. LATIN FORCE raced near the rear early, was steadied near the nine sixteenths, saved ground near the rear on the turn, began to edge forward near the quarter pole, swung out to the four path into the lane, and ran evenly between horses under a drive. RIDIN SOLO was extremely reluctant to load, raced toward the rear, was pushed along while saving ground on the turn, chased inside into the lane and offered no rally. BENZ LAKE THUNDER chased between horses down the backstretch, raced two wide toward the rear on the turn, was driven four wide into the lane and offered no rally. INCREEDIBLE VICTOR soon trailed, saved ground on the turn, was driven into the lane and proved no factor. CARPE GOLD was reluctant to load, chased the leading pair between MO MESA and GOT GHOSTED down the back straight, began to flatten out, chased in the three to four path on the turn, and came up empty in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 7 1M Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOTAL SURPRISE chased the leading line inside of RED'S MR Z into the first turn, continued in range down the back straight, ran on to stay in range of the dueling pair into the far turn, tipped three wide near the three eighths, engaged the leading pair, vied three wide in the lane, was carried out when TAHKODHA KNIGHT drifted out midstretch, and still outfinished FOUND JORDAN to prove best. FOUND JORDAN raced inside of CAUSEWAY SURPISE near the rear around the first turn, edged closer to the field in tandem with that foe down the back straight, tracked the leading trio in the three path on the far turn, shifted four wide into upper stretch, engaged outside the leading line inside the furlong mark, kept on willingly but was narrowly outkicked by the winner. CAT ON THE PROWL dueled inside of TAHKODHA KNIGHT through the first turn and down the backstretch, continued to battle inside that foe into the far turn, briefly did not go with that foe when TOTAL SURPRISE engaged on the outside, rerallied under a drive into the lane, led again midstretch, but was outfinished in the final sixteenth. TAHKODHA KNIGHT dueled with CAT ON THE PROWL while racing between horses through the first turn and down the backstretch, continued to vie outside of that horse into the far turn, battled inside of TOTAL SURPRISE when he rallied to the outside approaching the turn for home, battled between horses into the lane, drifted out into TOTAL SURPRISE midstretch and flattened in the final sixteenth. CAUSEWAY SURPISE raced two wide near the rear through the first turn, edged closer in tandem with FOUND JORDAN down the backstretch, chased behind that foe in the four path on the far turn, was driven in upper stretch and chased on mildly between horses. WHODOESITBETTER was reluctant to load, settled at the rear, trailed down the back straight, was driven in the four to five path on the far turn and passed some weakening horses, but lacked the needed rally in the lane. RED'S MR Z chased the leading line two wide through the first turn, continued to chase two wide down the back straight, began to weaken from just past the half and had no more in the lane. PRESTIGIOUSLY WILD tracked behind the leading line three wide early, tracked four wide down the backstretch, and emptied out from the half. IMAGINE DRAYGON raced three wide with the leading flight into the first turn, attended outside the dueling pair, backed off the near the nine sixteenths, gradually weakened between horses around the far turn and had no more in the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG PETE soon led, was well rated on the pace, kept on near the five sixteenths as UNIQUE PATH briefly loomed outside, kicked clear of that foe again near the quarter, went to a drive in upper stretch, maintained the lead and was geared down the last few jumps. DA GHOST chased two wide on the first turn, continued to chase three wide down the back straight, was urged for a three wide rally on the far turn and gained gradually, swung five wide into the lane, continued to pursue willingly, and got up for the place near the sixteenth mark while proving no match for the winner. UNIQUE PATH tracked the leader, loomed outside of BIG PETE near the five sixteenths, was shaken off by that foe past the quarter, proved no match inside though continued to chase with interest, and lost place near the sixteenth pole. TIGER HUNTER chased inside through the first turn, continued in close range inside down the back straight, tracked the leading pair inside around the far turn, swung four wide into upper stretch, chased on mildly but was ultimately outfinished. PUBLIC OPINION soon trailed, was driven in the five to six path on the far turn, came six wide into the lane, and passed tiring horses late while racing near the center of the course. RED CENTS chased the leading pair around the first turn, tracked outside of UNIQUE PATH down the back straight, did not go with that foe into the far turn, chased 2w between horses around the far turn, came into the lane four wide, and came up empty while drifting out. GLENDALE was pinched back in the opening strides due to TEXAS HOLDEM breaking outward, raced at the rear of the main pack inside that foe through the first turn, continued toward the rear down the backstretch, was urged into the far turn, but had no rally inside. TEXAS HOLDEM broke outward, raced at the rear of the main group outside of GLENDALE, inched forward between horses into the backstretch to take closer order, chased two wide around the far turn as the field stretched out, had no response and weakened.
